This article is a press release from the White House, announcing an executive order to adjust certain rates of pay. The order sets forth the rates of basic pay or salaries for various statutory pay systems, including the General Schedule, the Foreign Service Schedule, and the Veterans Health Administration. It also establishes the ranges of rates of basic pay for senior executives in the Senior Executive Service, and sets the rates of basic pay or salaries for certain executive, legislative, and judicial positions. Additionally, the order specifies the rates of monthly basic pay for members of the uniformed services and the rate of monthly cadet or midshipman pay. It also outlines the payments to be made for locality-based comparability and sets the rates of basic pay for administrative law judges. The effective dates for the different schedules are provided, and the order supersedes a prior executive order.